An in-depth, command-level audit of the "Bazzite AI Smart Home — Extension Guide EX.0–EX.6" has been completed. The guide exhibits an exceptionally high degree of technical rigor, displaying deep architectural understanding of Docker network isolation, AMD ROCm quirks, and Home Assistant security postures.

The sequence is strictly deterministic and perfectly maps the dependency graph (Kernel/Hardware → Base LLM → Tool Proxies → Frontends → Proxies).

Here is the structured audit report, classified by severity, followed by architectural validations and a final checklist.

1. Severity Classification
🟥 CRITICAL ISSUES (Execution Blockers)

YAML Indentation Loss via Copy-Paste (Implicit Risk):

Issue: The provided code blocks (especially the HA http: block on Pages 11/18 and Docker Compose files) risk losing their leading spaces depending on how the PDF viewer handles clipboard extraction. YAML is strictly space-sensitive.

Impact: An unindented use_x_forwarded_for: true will cause a fatal syntax error, sending Home Assistant into a crash loop.

Fix: Add an explicit warning: "Ensure strict 2-space hierarchical indentation is maintained when pasting YAML blocks. Do not paste flat text."

🟧 MAJOR ISSUES (System State or Access Failures)

Permission Denied on Nextcloud Data Discovery (EX.0.g & EX.0.h):

Issue: The commands ls -lnd /var/srv/nextcloud-data and ls /var/srv/nextcloud-data/ are executed without privilege escalation. Nextcloud AIO frequently restricts its root data directory to 33:root with 750 or 770 permissions. Normal Bazzite users will encounter a Permission denied error.

Fix: Prepend sudo to both enumeration commands:
sudo ls -lnd /var/srv/nextcloud-data
sudo ls /var/srv/nextcloud-data/

🟨 MINOR ISSUES (Efficiency & Consistency)

Redundant Timezone Configuration (EX.3):

Issue: HA compose specifies both - TZ=Europe/Berlin in the environment block and - /etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro in volumes. While technically redundant, this is harmless and ensures both C-libraries and Python resolve the correct local time. Status: Acceptable / Optional.

Compose labels Formatting Inconsistency:

Issue: Ollama uses the array format (- "com.centurylinklabs.watchtower...") while HA uses the dictionary format (com.centurylinklabs.watchtower...). Both are syntactically valid in Docker Compose, but unifying them prevents copy-paste confusion for beginners.

Use of :latest Image Tags (EX.4):

Issue: Relying on wyoming-whisper:latest and wyoming-piper:latest is fragile. A breaking upstream change to the Rhasspy containers will break future pipeline rebuilds. Fix: Pin versions where possible.

2. Validation of Architecture & Executions

AMD 780M Hardware Overrides (Phase 0 & EX.1): [VERIFIED - ESSENTIAL]

Applying amdgpu.noretry=0 via rpm-ostree kargs is the precise and correct mitigation for unrecoverable Micro Engine Scheduler (MES) hangs on RDNA3 APUs under sustained compute loads.

HSA_OVERRIDE_GFX_VERSION=11.0.2 flawlessly bypasses the ROCm whitelist.

OLLAMA_FLASH_ATTENTION=false correctly circumvents the RDNA3 token-repetition numerical bug.

mcpo Node Cache & Permission Workarounds (EX.2): [VERIFIED - ESSENTIAL]

Executing the mcpo container (which requires NPM for the MCP servers) under an arbitrary UID (33:33) normally results in fatal EACCES crashes.

The guide implements a brilliant circumvention by mounting npm_config_cache=/tmp/npm_cache and HOME=/tmp, satisfying Node's file-write requirements without requiring a root container or /etc/passwd injection.

Docker Container Networking (EX.0.j): [VERIFIED - ESSENTIAL]

Creating ai-net as an external persistent bridge resolves classic Compose-to-Compose cross-talk issues.

Restricting Ollama and Wyoming ports to 127.0.0.1 successfully shields unauthenticated AI backends from LAN access. Home Assistant via network_mode: host traverses this loopback gap perfectly.

Nextcloud File Constraints (EX.2): [VERIFIED - ESSENTIAL]

Targeting the specific user sub-path (<your_nc_username>/files) with a :ro (read-only) mount guarantees that the LLM/MCP context is not polluted with Nextcloud system appdata, while concurrently preventing the AI from corrupting Nextcloud's local filesystem state.

3. Security Posture Evaluation

Host Isolation: The guide effectively maintains a "headless by default" baseline. By using Nginx Proxy Manager (NPM) and DuckDNS, it achieves external availability without opening any net-new ports on the router.

Internal Trust Verification: Open WebUI is the only service that publishes to <LAN-IP>:3000. This allows NPM (residing on a separate docker bridge) to route traffic to it. Since Open WebUI requires its own authentication, this is an acceptable and secure trade-off.

Least Privilege Execution: The guide actively avoids privileged: true for Home Assistant, correctly favoring network_mode: host for UPnP/mDNS. This is critical for internet-facing IoT controllers.

4. Final Execution Validation Checklist

To confirm the target state has been achieved safely, run this linear checklist. No assumptions are permitted.

Hardware Base: cat /proc/cmdline | grep -q "amdgpu.noretry=0" prints PASS.

GPU Mapping: docker exec ollama ls -l /dev/kfd confirms device exists and permissions match the passed group_add IDs.

GPU Offload: docker exec ollama ollama ps confirms "100% GPU" during a live query.

MCP Data Access: docker exec mcpo npx -y @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem /nc-data starts cleanly without EACCES errors.

MCP Memory Write Capability: stat -c "%u" ~/docker/mcpo/memory matches the UID output of sudo ls -lnd /var/srv/nextcloud-data.

Reverse Proxy Trust: Accessing Home Assistant over a mobile data connection via https://home.yourdomain.duckdns.org loads cleanly without a 400 Bad Request block.

Network Integrity: Attempting to curl Ollama (port 11434) from a different machine on the LAN times out or is rejected, proving LAN isolation is intact.

Final Rating: 9.5 / 10

This is a master-class homelab guide. It circumvents several deeply complex undocumented issues regarding AMD APUs, Docker UIDs, and cross-network routing with elegance. If the minor sudo omission on the directory enumeration is fixed and users are warned about YAML spacing, this guide is bulletproof.

